# Quality Workflow

Run these steps after **every** code change before considering work done.

## 1. LSP Diagnostics

- **Go** (`pkg/`): Check the Problems panel for gopls errors — fix ALL errors and warnings
- **TypeScript** (`src/`): Check the Problems panel — fix ALL errors and warnings

## 2. Code Review

Use the `code-review` skill on modified files. Fix ALL critical, major, and medium severity issues.

## 3. Code Simplification

Use the `code-simplifier` skill. Apply clarity improvements without changing behavior.

## 4. Remove AI Slop

Use the `/remove-ai-code-slop` Cursor command. Remove:
- Comments that just restate what the code does
- Empty or catch-and-log-only catch blocks
- Unnecessary defensive checks in trusted call paths
- `any` casts used to work around type issues

## 5. Tests & Lint

```bash
# Always prefix npm commands with nvm use 22 &&
nvm use 22 && npm run test:ci        # Frontend unit tests
go test ./pkg/...                    # Backend tests
nvm use 22 && npm run lint           # ESLint
nvm use 22 && npm run typecheck      # TypeScript
nvm use 22 && npm run validate:openapi  # Only if HTTP endpoints changed
```

Fix every failure — iterate until all pass.

## 6. Pre-PR Review

Before commit, run the `/run-all-tests-and-fix` command, then use the `pr-review-toolkit` skill
for a comprehensive review. Fix all critical/major/medium issues from code-reviewer,
silent-failure-hunter, and type-design-analyzer.

## 7. Commit & PR Title Format (CI-enforced)

**PR title** and **every commit** in the branch are validated by GitHub Actions. Use this format or CI fails.

**Format:** `type(scope): description` (scope optional but recommended)

**Allowed types:** `feat` `fix` `docs` `style` `refactor` `perf` `test` `build` `ci` `chore` `revert`

**Allowed scopes:** `chat` `mcp` `session` `config` `rbac` `oauth` `share` `viz` `backend` `ui` `frontend` `deps` `release` `ci` `main`

**Rules:** Imperative subject, lowercase, no period at end. PR title must match exactly (e.g. `docs: add Cursor agent rules`). Unscoped is valid: `docs: update README`.

**Workflows:** `.github/workflows/pr-title.yml` (PR title), `.github/workflows/commitlint.yml` (commits).

## Severity Policy

| Severity | Action |
|----------|--------|
| Critical | Fix immediately — security, data loss, crashes |
| Major | Fix before commit — logic errors, missing error handling, RBAC |
| Medium | Fix before PR — code smells, missing validation |
| Low/Info | Fix if trivial, otherwise note as tech debt |
